videos.description: Missouri quarterback Drew Lock throws a long pass into double coverage and is intercepted by CJ Henderson in the end zone.
videos.headline: Florida forces turnover on first drive

videos.description: What looks like a routine punt turns into a massive break for the Tigers as Florida's Brandon Powell fumbles the punt return deep in Gator territory.
videos.headline: Muffed punt puts Missouri in scoring position

videos.description: Tigers' quarterback Drew Lock throws it up for Kendall Blanton who gets one foot down in the end zone to put Missouri up 7-0 against Florida.
videos.headline: Missouri strikes first with Lock TD pass

videos.description: Missouri's Drew Lock finds Emanuel Hall streaking down field and connects on a long pass for a gain of 36 yards into Florida territory.
videos.headline: Hall goes up and over Florida defender for catch

videos.description: Missouri's running back Larry Roundtree III lowers his shoulder and burrows into the end zone as the Tigers take a 14-0 lead over the Gators in the first half.
videos.headline: Roundtree cannot be stopped at the goal line

videos.description: Tigers' quarterback Drew Lock throws it deep downfield and J'Mon Moore turns on the burners to haul in the 38-yard pass.
videos.headline: Moore burns Florida secondary to get into red zone

videos.description: The Missouri offensive line picks up the blitz and buys Drew Lock enough time to deliver a beautiful ball to Ish Witter to make it 21-3 in the first half.
videos.headline: Lock drops ball in behind Florida defense for TD

videos.description: Missouri's Anthony Sherrils undercuts Malik Zaire's pass and intercepts the ball to give the Tigers the ball in Gators' territory.
videos.headline: Missouri defense intercepts Zaire

videos.description: Missouri's Larry Roundtree III runs through the heart of the Florida defense for the tough 21-yard score to put the Tigers up 28-3 before half.
videos.headline: Roundtree rips Florida's defense for second score

videos.description: Florida interim head coach Randy Shannon says that Florida's offense was able to put points on the board in the first half, but penalties wiped out big plays.
videos.headline: Shannon hopes better blocking will change momentum

videos.description: Florida's Malik Zaire looks like he will be sacked, but he spins and escapes the tackle to flip a shovel-pass to Lamical Perine before he gets clobbered by a Missouri defender.
videos.headline: Florida's Zaire escapes sack, converts miraculous first down

videos.description: Drew Lock connects with deep threat Emanuel Hall for 49 yards to the goal line.
videos.headline: Missouri's Lock unleashes cannon arm to set up TD

videos.description: Missouri's Larry Roundtree III scores his third touchdown of the day on a powerful goal line run as the Tigers lead the Gators 35-9.
videos.headline: Tigers' Roundtree rumbles for third score

videos.description: Drew Lock fires a pass to J'Mon Moore for the four-yard score that puts the Tigers up 42-9.
videos.headline: Missouri's Lock continues big day with third TD pass

videos.description: Feleipe Franks comes in for Malik Zaire and throws a touchdown pass to Lamical Perine in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Florida's Franks throws TD in relief

videos.description: Missouri head coach Barry Odom says he challenged his team to have a fast start, and the Tigers delivered with a "full game" in their 45-16 win over Florida.
videos.headline: Fast start guides Missouri to first conference win
